    II. CONCLUSION
Accessibility, security, and failures on the database metrics were determined, their values were examined, and possible solutions were reported through references and examples.
It is possible to prevent database failures and security vulnerabilities that may occur in the database through methodologies, created algorithms and Oracle's software packages.
However, in backup strategies, the RMAN methodology shows that it will give faster and more robust results compared to the backup methodology applied when the database is closed and open.
At the same time mirroring methodology can provides opportunity to use database without interrupting.
But ultimately, the biggest role in database systems, whether it's Oracle software packages or best-functioning algorithm, only can work it on best possible with administrators' job tracking.




























